abstract: A Pennsylvania appeals court on Tuesday dismissed Bill Cosby's bid to overturn his 2018 sex assault conviction, rejecting his lawyers' argument that a judge deprived the comedian of a fair trial by allowing other accusers to testify.
snippet: A Pennsylvania appeals court on Tuesday dismissed Bill Cosby's bid to overturn his 2018 sex assault conviction, rejecting his lawyers' argument that a judge deprived the comedian of a fair trial by allowing other accusers to testify.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - A Pennsylvania appeals court on Tuesday dismissed Bill Cosby's bid to overturn his 2018 sex assault conviction, rejecting his lawyers' argument that a judge deprived the comedian of a fair trial by allowing other accusers to testify.
headline_main: Pennsylvania Court Rejects Bill Cosby's Appeal of Sex Assault Conviction
headline_print_headline: Pennsylvania Court Rejects Bill Cosby's Appeal of Sex Assault Conviction

abstract: “Love, Actually” is all around this year in Britain’s pre-Christmas election.
snippet: “Love, Actually” is all around this year in Britain’s pre-Christmas election.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — “Love, Actually” is all around this year in Britain’s pre-Christmas election.

headline_print_headline: Holiday Rom-Com 'Love, Actually' Inspires UK Election Memes

abstract: The European Commission said it would only consider money-laundering reforms after it completes a thorough assessment of the issue, dashing hopes the EU executive would act rapidly to crack down on dirty money flowing through the continent.
snippet: The European Commission said it would only consider money-laundering reforms after it completes a thorough assessment of the issue, dashing hopes the EU executive would act rapidly to crack down on dirty money flowing through the continent.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Commission said it would only consider money-laundering reforms after it completes a thorough assessment of the issue, dashing hopes the EU executive would act rapidly to crack down on dirty money flowing through the continent.
headline_main: 'Less Action Plans, More Action': EU Commission Under Fire Over Money-Laundering Overhaul
headline_print_headline: 'Less Action Plans, More Action': EU Commission Under Fire Over Money-Laundering Overhaul

abstract: Sterling edged up to a seven-month high against the dollar on Tuesday, cementing recent gains as traders shrugged off weak economic growth data and kept an eye on the final days of campaigning before Britain's general election.
snippet: Sterling edged up to a seven-month high against the dollar on Tuesday, cementing recent gains as traders shrugged off weak economic growth data and kept an eye on the final days of campaigning before Britain's general election.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Sterling edged up to a seven-month high against the dollar on Tuesday, cementing recent gains as traders shrugged off weak economic growth data and kept an eye on the final days of campaigning before Britain's general election.
headline_main: Sterling Hits a Seven-Month High as Election Nears
headline_print_headline: Sterling Hits a Seven-Month High as Election Nears

abstract: The Kremlin is blaming political chicanery, not its own sports officials, after doctored laboratory data resulted in a ban that means Russia will appear on the global sports stage without its flag or anthem for the next four years.
snippet: The Kremlin is blaming political chicanery, not its own sports officials, after doctored laboratory data resulted in a ban that means Russia will appear on the global sports stage without its flag or anthem for the next four years.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — The Kremlin is blaming political chicanery, not its own sports officials, after doctored laboratory data resulted in a ban that means Russia will appear on the global sports stage without its flag or anthem for the next four years.
headline_main: Russia Blames Political Chicanery, Not Itself, for Olympic Ban
headline_print_headline: Russia Blames Political Chicanery, Not Itself, for Olympic Ban

abstract: The Trump administration on Tuesday imposed economic sanctions on more than a dozen individuals suspected of human rights violations in six countries and banned two others from entering the United States, including a former Saudi official in Turkey for his alleged role in the murder of Saudi journalist Jamal Khashoggi.
snippet: The Trump administration on Tuesday imposed economic sanctions on more than a dozen individuals suspected of human rights violations in six countries and banned two others from entering the United States, including a former Saudi official in Turke...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Tuesday imposed economic sanctions on more than a dozen individuals suspected of human rights violations in six countries and banned two others from entering the United States, including a former Saudi official in Turkey for his alleged role in the murder of Saudi journalist Jamal Khashoggi.
headline_main: US Sanctions Individuals Suspected of Human Rights Abuses
headline_print_headline: US Sanctions Individuals Suspected of Human Rights Abuses

abstract: Delivering on a campaign promise to teachers who helped elect him, Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear used his first day in office Tuesday to overhaul the state school board.
snippet: Delivering on a campaign promise to teachers who helped elect him, Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear used his first day in office Tuesday to overhaul the state school board.
lead_paragraph: FRANKFORT, Ky. — Delivering on a campaign promise to teachers who helped elect him, Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear used his first day in office Tuesday to overhaul the state school board.
headline_main: Kentucky's New Governor Reorganizes School Board on Day One
headline_print_headline: Kentucky's New Governor Reorganizes School Board on Day One

abstract: The administration’s food stamp cuts expose the cruel truth of Republican hypocrisy.
snippet: The administration’s food stamp cuts expose the cruel truth of Republican hypocrisy.
lead_paragraph: The Trump administration is highly selective in how it applies the standard of “self-sufficiency” for programs. To move food stamp beneficiaries toward that goal in all states, Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue laid out a plan to strengthen work requirements for federal beneficiaries by April 2020.
